HEADWORD: Semicolon
<hw>Sem"i*co`lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The punctuation
mark [;] indicating a separation between parts or members of a sentence
more distinct than that marked by a comma.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semicolumn</ent>⟦br⟧
